arch:property.oc:show_val: Total includes artifacts from 1/4" screen samples and >4mm fraction of bulk samples, excluding botanicals, shell, and unmodified vert fauna (weight only), and 1/8" screen samples. See tables 3-1 and 3-2 and Appendix A in survey report.
THE TEMPORAL COMPONENTS APPEAR TO BE SEPERATED VERTICALLY WITH ST. JOHNS 0-40CMBS, ORANGE 30-70CMBS, AND ARCHAIC LITHIC 60-120CMBS. ALL PERIODS ARE DISTRIBUTED HORIZONTALLY OVER SITE AREA.
Deposits investigated here entirely of Mount Taylor age, though rare corner-/side-notched bifaces and fiber-tempred pottery suggests earlier and later components in the vicinity.
